CAPE TOWN – At least one person has died after a blaze ripped through another informal settlement in Cape Town. READ: Hundreds displaced after Cape Town fire With just a week to go before schools reopen, some residents have lost everything, including new school uniforms and stationery. Some 400 people are now homeless and a 44-year-old man died in Monday evening’s fire in Langa, which razed 159 shacks to the ground. Authorities and residents have no idea how the fire started, with locals saying all they want from the municipality is proper housing. Once all the rubble is cleared, fire kits to help rebuild will be issued. eNCA